# Test modules
#
# We intentionally do NOT list CPython's internal test/example modules here
# (_testcapi, _testinternalcapi, _testlimitedcapi, _testbuffer, _testclinic*,
# _testimportmultiple, _testmultiphase, _testsinglephase, _ctypes_test,
# _xxtestfuzz, xxsubtype, xxlimited, xxlimited_35). The build already passes
# --disable-test-modules; previously listing them here OVERRODE that flag and
# forced them to build (the configure summary reported "0 disabled").
#
# In 3.14 this actively broke the install: the _testcapi/_testinternalcapi/
# _testlimitedcapi source-file lists must be enumerated by hand and upstream
# added new files (e.g. _testcapi/weakref.c -> _PyTestCapi_Init_Weakref,
# _testinternalcapi/complex.c, _testlimitedcapi/version.c). With the stale
# lists the .so linked but failed to import ("symbol not found"), so 3.14
# renamed them <mod>_failed.so and `make sharedinstall` then died with
# "cannot stat 'Modules/_testinternalcapi...so'".
#
# These modules have no place in a lean bootable rootfs, and hand-maintaining
# their per-version source lists is exactly the kind of non-reproducible churn
# we want to avoid. Letting --disable-test-modules do its job drops them all.
